вҠў seed
  given phrase вүЎ "The cat sat on the mat"
  given target-lang вүЎ "French"
  yield phrase, target-lang

  вҠЁ phrase is a complete English sentence
  вҠЁ target-lang is a natural language name

вҠў translate
  given seedвҶ’phrase
  given seedвҶ’target-lang
  yield translation, confidence

  вҲҙ Translate В«seedвҶ’phraseВ» into В«seedвҶ’target-langВ».
    Yield the translated text as В«translationВ».
    Rate your confidence from 0.0 to 1.0 as В«confidenceВ».

  вҠЁ translation is in В«seedвҶ’target-langВ»
  вҠЁ confidence вҲҲ [0.0, 1.0]

  вҠЁ? on failure:
    retry with В«oracle.failuresВ» appended to prompt
    max 2

  вҠЁ? on exhaustion:
    error-value(вҠҘ)

вҠў back-translate
  given translateвҶ’translation
  yield round-trip

  вҲҙ Translate В«translateвҶ’translationВ» back into English.
    Yield the result as В«round-tripВ».

  вҠЁ round-trip is in English

  вҠҘ? skip with round-trip вҶҗ "вҠҘ: translation failed"

вҠў verify
  given seedвҶ’phrase
  given back-translateвҶ’round-trip
  yield verdict, fidelity-score

  вҠў= fidelity-score вҶҗ levenshtein_similarity(seedвҶ’phrase, back-translateвҶ’round-trip)

  вҲҙ Compare the original phrase "В«seedвҶ’phraseВ»" with the round-trip
    translation "В«back-translateвҶ’round-tripВ»".
    If they convey the same meaning, verdict is "faithful".
    If meaning shifted, verdict is "drifted".
    If the round-trip contains "вҠҘ", verdict is "failed".

  вҠЁ verdict вҲҲ {"faithful", "drifted", "failed"}
  вҠЁ fidelity-score вҲҲ [0.0, 1.0]
